<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at a stroke • at the stroke</xh5><p> <i>at a stroke—</i>suddenly and with a single action or effort: Some companies were in trouble because Mr. Heath changed strategy <u>at a stroke</u>.</p><p> <i>at the stroke—</i>at exactly the time stated or agreed upon: We agreed to meet for lunch, and he arrived <u>at the stroke</u>.</p> </entry>
